post_text:
2020 School tax bills for Chichester School District property owners are being mailed on June 30, 2020. Tax bills are only mailed to the property owner of record per the County Board of Assessment records, not to a designated finance or mortgage company. The homeowner must forward the tax bill to these companies for processing. Contact the Board of Assessment at 610-891-4879 for changes.

Effect of Failure to Receive a Tax Notice. (Local Tax Collection Law, Section 7)
Failure to receive notice shall not relieve any taxpayer from the payment of any taxes imposed by any taxing district, and such taxpayer shall be charged with his taxes as though he had received notice. Homeowners not receiving a tax bill, should contact the tax collector for your municipality.

Upper Chichester Township

Kimberly Riley, kriley@upperchitwp.org

Lower Chichester Township, Trainer Borough, Marcus Hook Borough

Lauri Lewis, (610) 485-6881, ext. 5004, llewis@chichestersd.org

A Junior Class Parent erroneously posted on Facebook that Concordville Inn will not return the deposit for the Junior Prom. Please know that was not accurate. Our school district continues to have a strong and consistent relationship with Concordville Inn, and they have worked with our Class Advisors to apply that deposit to next year’s Junior Prom. Keeping in mind that banquet halls like Concordville Inn rely on a positive social media presence, we wish to properly reflect the repeated and successful events at Concordville Inn.

Thank you,

Paul Amand

Director of Student Activities & Athletics

Chichester School District

post_text: Congratulations to our 8th grade (now 9thgrade) students! Although it wasn’t the “goodbye” we hoped to give our students as we typically do with our “Move Up” Day, we want to thank all of the students, their families, and teachers for coming out to celebrate our graduates with a celebratory parade. It was a festive day with posters, balloons, and music. We wish our graduates all the best in high school and we will miss them very much!

post_text:
School Reopening Survey

Return to School Survey

The Chichester School District's Return to School Task Force has been meeting to discuss options for next school year. In June, a survey was sent to parents asking for their feedback in our initial planning phase. The results of the survey have been used to help design three options for next year. The options are designed to be flexible and can be instituted based on the Governor's recommendations for social distancing and safety practices. Please take a moment to answer this brief survey so we can finalize our plans for the 2020-2021 year. Please note that the survey will close on July 7th. Here is the link to the survey: https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/2020-2021returnplan

We have a special announcement!
During spring break staff will be given time off to rest and spend time with their family. On Friday, April 3 each student will be given 5 days of lunch and breakfast for spring break, meals will not include pork products. Beginning Monday, April 13 our meal pick up schedule will be 2 days a week, Monday and Wednesday. Monday’s pick up will include breakfast and lunch for Tuesday and Wednesday. Wednesday’s pick up will include breakfast and lunch for Thursday, Friday and Monday. This is being done for the safety of families and our staff. Please check the website for our updated menu and schedule.
The Chichester Food Service staff would like to thank you for your support and wish you and your families a happy and safe spring break.

Boothwyn: 12:00 pm – 12:45 pm Hilltop: 1:45 pm – 2:30 pm

Students can report to the closest location and this is for any school aged child living around these locations.

post_text:
Congratulations to Brian Duffey, our Teacher of the Month at Chichester Middle School ! This month's theme was 'diligent and hardworking' and that certainly is Brian. Duffey works tirelessly to help all of his students to achieve and be all that they can be. We are so thankful for his enthusiasm and dedication to Chichester Middle School.

Here are a few things that his peers have said about Bryan:

Duff spends an inordinate amount of time working with and for the students of Chichester Middle School!

Bryan has helped bring a new course- Algebra I- to CMS and has run with it. He is always willing to go above and beyond, he is a team player and puts the kids first.

Duff is always working, creating new lessons for both his Algebra class and his other math classes. He spends many hours working at home on engaging lesson planning and grading.

post_text:
Yesterday, six high school students traveled to Penn State University to participate in the Mini-THON Appreciation Breakfast where they networked with students from other schools who are also holding Mini-THON events this year. They also heard from guest speakers including Charles Millard, the founder of the Four Diamonds Fund (the beneficiary of the fundraising efforts of our Mini-THON and the larger student-run event at Penn State), and Tucker Haas, a Penn State freshman and cancer survivor, thanks to the money that has been raised for the Four Diamonds Fund.

The first ever Chichester Mini-THON will be taking place in the gym at Chichester High School on Friday, February 28 from 4:00-10:00pm. There will be games, food, music, and activities to fill the six hours to raise awareness and funds for childhood cancer. In a similar fashion to THON weekend at Penn State, our final fundraising total will be revealed at the end of the event!

Spread the word, tell your friends, and let’s dance For The Kids! “One day, we will dance in celebration. Until then, we will dance for a cure!”

post_text: BEARs: Be Excited About Reading happened at Marcus Hook Today! This tradition started a few years ago where every student goes home with a free book to keep forever and always. Students are encouraged to read the book and then either keep it or share it with a friend (or even return it to their teacher to place it in their classroom library.) Our used books are donated by community members and also by a local non-profit organization called Treasures for Educators! Thank you to all of them for making BEARs a huge success year after year!

post_text: Last evening several members of Rho Kappa, along with some friends, volunteered their time to bring a little holiday cheer to our brave men and women serving overseas this holiday season. Established in 2003, the Delaware based project strives to bring a “touch of home” as a way of showing appreciation to our troops who are actively serving. Not only was Chichester able to make donations through our drive, student volunteers unpacked, sorted, and stuffed personalized stockings with treats, necessities, and messages of appreciation. If you, or your family are interested in participating please see the link https://www.stockingsforsoldiers.org. Here are pictures of their hard work.

post_text: Students had an amazing experience going to the Delaware County Court House yesterday. Students enjoyed a brief tour of downtown Media followed by lunch. Hope you enjoy the pictures.

post_text:
Tonight's football game at Interboro is being rescheduled due to a potential threat of a weapon being brought to the game by a student. The Interboro School District Administration, along with the police departments supporting Interboro have been investigating and communicating with our administration and police departments. As a result, they have determined that to ensure the safety of the students, staff, and community that it was better to reschedule the game this evening. The athletic directors from both schools are working to reschedule the game and Mr. Amand will communicate the new date and time as soon as one is scheduled. Thank you and have a good evening.

Dr. Gregory Puckett
Assistant Superintendent
Chichester School District
401 Cherry Tree Road
Aston, PA 19014
610-485-6881

Congrats to Chichester Middle School’s September Teacher of the Month, Mrs. Busz!

Mrs. Busz was nominated by her colleagues for the following reasons:

• Whenever I see her she is always smiling! She is willing to donate lots of time to various clubs and activities. She tries to improve the climate and culture of the building. She is a great person to be around!

• Busz goes above and beyond for her students. She is dedicated to supporting the PBS team and gave of a lot of her own time to ensure that the 5/6 social went perfectly.

• PBIS would also like to thank Chrissy for all of the time she spent planning, organizing, and hosting the 5/6 Social. So many kids enjoyed the time at school and had fun.

post_text: On September 5, 2019, members of the Riddle Memorial Hospital Emergency Department delivered over 5 containers of items for the Chichester School District pantries. Each year Chichester School District seeks donations for its pantries in support of its students and families. Riddle Emergency Department Unit Council collected items from the nurses and staff in the department. The items were delivered to the Chichester Education Center where they will be distributed to each building’s pantry. School Board President Ruth Ann Baiocco and Superintendent Dan Nerelli thanks the Emergency Department from Riddle Memorial Hospital for the generous donations.

It is with great sadness on behalf of the Chichester School Board, and Staff we ask that you keep Dave Disands, and his family in your thoughts. Dave is one of our School Resource Officers and is part of our district family, along with the Upper Chichester Police Department. In a tragic accident on July 11th, Matthew Disands, Dave’s son lost his life suddenly. There are no words to describe the heartbreak that the family is going through at this time, and we will do what a family does and support the Disands family anyway we can.
Ruth Ann Baiocco
Board President

Dear Chichester School District Community,
Beginning on Monday July 15, 2019 through Monday August 12, 2019, the running track located at Chichester High School, 3333 Chichester Avenue, Upper Chichester, PA 19061 will be CLOSED to any/all use by the community or groups.
Resurfacing of the track will result in a finished product with a better surface, and extended use to all the community to enjoy for years to come.
We apologize in advance for any inconvenience this may cause. Community cooperation during this time will ensure a successful projection completion.
Any questions or concerns during the project can be directed to the Chichester Maintenance Office @ 610-485-6881 Ext. 6402.
Thanks,
Mike Civera
Interim Facilities Director

post_text:
Last week, Marcus Hook celebrated “Decades Week” in honor of our building being over 100 years old.

Tuesday was Guest Reader Day. Former teachers and administrators return to read to our children and tell tales from when they were here.
Wednesday was Decades Day. Each grade dressed in clothes representing different decades.
On Thursday, we had a tree planting, Buddy Bench dedication and revealed a time capsule that was found during the renovation.
Friday was Fun Day.
